&lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Typing a password every time I connect to a machine is a hassle (mostly because I keep forgetting it).&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="one-click-setup">One-Click Setup
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>If your computer doesn&amp;rsquo;t have a public key yet, you need to generate one. It&amp;rsquo;s usually located at &lt;code>~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">ssh-keygen
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Then, run the following command on your local machine:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">ssh-copy-id username@RemoteIP
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Replace &lt;code>username&lt;/code> with the account you want to log into, and &lt;code>RemoteIP&lt;/code> with the target IP address.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>